Veteran singer, Daddy Showkey has disclosed plans to launch a new app meant to facilitate and promote indigenous interaction. In an interview with Hip TV, the popular ‘Galala’ singer discussed what he’s been working on for a while. He said he’s about to launch an indigenous interaction app named ‘Confam Made.’ According to him: “’Confam Made’ is like you’re talking about Facebook but is Nigerian, it’s African. It’s first of its kind in Africa.   Falz, Timaya, Skales storm Yung Willis private birthday in…     Let me die if I can’t take bullet for Davido, says PA     Pastor Ibiyeomie curses yahoo yahoo boys   - Advertisement - “It’s something you can claim responsibility that this is your own. Your own platform where you can reach every body. ‘Confam Made’ first of all is a Nigerian app and an African app right now. But anywhere you are in the world, you can access ‘Confam Made’. But we are under ‘test run’ right now. On his reason why he decided to create the app, the 51-year-old Ghetto singer explained his decision was informed based on the fact that he represents an original brand which is his logo. Giving more insights into the app, Showkey said: “First of all, Confam Made is about something like, this is your own thing. This is our own thing. “You need to be proud of who you are to confirm that you like the way you look, you like the way you do things. You have to be proud of things that are your own. That’s what ‘Confam Made’ is about.”